1. Prior to stripping temporary support, contractor to confirm with structural engineer minimum
concrete strength requirements. Concrete strength shall not be less than 70
2. Concrete strength to be determined by field cured cylinders.
3. Stripping & reshoring shall be done on same day . Do not leave unreshored slab overnight.
4. During stripping & reshoring operation, at least one complete bay to be cleared before any reshores are installed.
5. Place reshores as laid out on plan, denoted by ' X ' for # 2 post shore TYP.
6. All equipment must be inspected by contractor prior to use. Bent or damaged equipment should not be used.
7. Vertical posts or frames must be within 1/2 " of plumb and must be checked prior to concrete placement .
8. Contractor shall submit reshore plans to designer of the permanent structure for acceptance in accordance
9. Prior to use, inspection by the undersigned P. Eng. is required . ( 48 hrs. notice , please ).
